"n.辩论的场所，讲坛 【记】 参考：forensic(辩论 的，法庭的) 【例】 The letters page of this newspaper is a forum for public argument. n. (用于审判活动和公众事务的)古罗马广场; 公开讨论会; 公共集会场地; 论坛, 法庭 = tribunal 【参】forensic(adj 辩论的, 法庭的): 佛和人中死了一个 【记】for向，去 + room 去房间咱们谈谈 forum (n.)  mid-15c., ""place of assembly in ancient Rome,"" from Latin forum ""marketplace, open space, public place,"" apparently akin to foris, foras ""out of doors, outside,"" from PIE root *dhwer- (see door). Sense of ""assembly, place for public discussion"" first recorded 1680s."
